<div id="review_1969323988" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1969323988" />
    <a title="mwana" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/32149976-mwana"><img alt="mwana" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1641648577p2/32149976.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1969323988?book_show_action=true">Apr 12, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="mwana" class="user" itemprop="url" name="mwana" href="/user/show/32149976-mwana">mwana</a>
      </span>

          added it




        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32149976-mwana?shelf=classic">classic</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32149976-mwana?shelf=not-for-me">not-for-me</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1969323988" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8846984353948015244">No rating.<br/><br/>I read this book in high school. It was a set book. And I hated it. Not because the writing is bad or because I felt it was some kind of political analogy but because it was text book to me. Reading it was a chore I would have preferred not to do. At all. Like ironing clothes or emptying my cat&apos;s litter box. Bleurgh!!!<br/><br/>I don&apos;t even recall most of it. All I remember was lots of sewage. Lots of opposition. And the groaning drone of my high school English teacher (who didn&apos;t like me, btw) </span>
  <span id="freeText8846984353948015244" style="display:none">No rating.<br><br>I read this book in high school. It was a set book. And I hated it. Not because the writing is bad or because I felt it was some kind of political analogy but because it was text book to me. Reading it was a chore I would have preferred not to do. At all. Like ironing clothes or emptying my cat's litter box. Bleurgh!!!<br><br>I don't even recall most of it. All I remember was lots of sewage. Lots of opposition. And the groaning drone of my high school English teacher (who didn't like me, btw) as he blathered on about how the title is an antonym because of some kind of political persuasion because of... <br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1491590931ra/22426550.gif" width="500" height="219" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>I can already hear my cells falling asleep. So I'll stop there. And take a walk. This book is recommended to anyone who didn't have to go through my English classes in high school.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8846984353948015244" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

