<div id="review_1442437850" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1442437850" />
    <a title="Laura" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/34293771-laura"><img alt="Laura" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1643761873p2/34293771.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1442437850?book_show_action=true">Oct 08, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Laura" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Laura" href="/user/show/34293771-laura">Laura</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="paper 9780486406572" href="/book/show/753043.An_Enemy_of_the_People">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/34293771-laura?shelf=victorian">victorian</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/34293771-laura?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/34293771-laura?shelf=scandinavian">scandinavian</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1442437850" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6824587488837405240">In response to the poor reception of his play &quot;Ghosts,&quot; Ibsen wrote &quot;An Enemy of the People.&quot; Dr. Stockmann discovers that the Municipal Baths in his hometown are contaminated, and believes he is doing good for the community. He is declared an enemy of the people when he addresses the ignorant and powerful majority. At this point, Dr. Stockmann discovers a far more serious problem.</span>
  <span id="freeText6824587488837405240" style="display:none">In response to the poor reception of his play "Ghosts," Ibsen wrote "An Enemy of the People." Dr. Stockmann discovers that the Municipal Baths in his hometown are contaminated, and believes he is doing good for the community. He is declared an enemy of the people when he addresses the ignorant and powerful majority. At this point, Dr. Stockmann discovers a far more serious problem.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6824587488837405240" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
