<div id="review_1010523408" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1010523408" />
    <a title="Sarah" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/31533844-sarah"><img alt="Sarah" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1617809291p2/31533844.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1010523408?book_show_action=true">Jul 29, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sarah" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sarah" href="/user/show/31533844-sarah">Sarah</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/31533844-sarah?shelf=plays">plays</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/31533844-sarah?shelf=i-had-to-read-this-for-school">i-had-to-read-this-for-school</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/31533844-sarah?shelf=scandinavian-lit">scandinavian-lit</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1010523408" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10436418345398749047"><i>An Enemy of the People</i> is an interesting play, mainly because it applies so much to attitudes about some subjects nowadays in modern times (environment issues- are we destroying the ozone layer?). It is very telling of the hypocrisy of the government and of politics. In thid play, the main character discovers that the famous hot springs in his own town are polluted and could cause many people to become sick. However, the somewhat corrupt political system denies this from an economic standpoint w</span>
  <span id="freeText10436418345398749047" style="display:none"><i>An Enemy of the People</i> is an interesting play, mainly because it applies so much to attitudes about some subjects nowadays in modern times (environment issues- are we destroying the ozone layer?). It is very telling of the hypocrisy of the government and of politics. In thid play, the main character discovers that the famous hot springs in his own town are polluted and could cause many people to become sick. However, the somewhat corrupt political system denies this from an economic standpoint while swaying the citizens of the town to turn against the main character. <br /><br />Many of Ibsen's plays do not seem dated or archaic at all- this play is a prime example of that. As I stated before, there are a lot of conflicts that have been covered up to avoid economic issues. I enjoy reading a protest in play form, because Ibsen can do it well. Overall, this play is insightful, applicable, and entertaining as a drama. </span>
  <a data-text-id="10436418345398749047" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


